Package: zcashd-node
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Conflicts: zcashd
Replaces: zcashd
Description: P2P Zcash daemon - node variant without wallet support (no GUI)
 Zcash is an implementation of the "Zerocash" protocol.
 Based on Bitcoin's code, it intends to offer a far higher standard
 of privacy and anonymity through a sophisticiated zero-knowledge
 proving scheme which preserves confidentiality of transaction metadata.
 This package provides the daemon, zcashd, and the CLI tool,
 zcash-cli, to interact with the daemon.
 .
 This package provides zcashd, a combined daemon and CLI tool to
 interact with the daemon.

Package: zcashd-wallet
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Conflicts: zcashd
Replaces: zcashd
Description: P2P Zcash daemon - full variant wallet support (no GUI)
 Zcash is an implementation of the "Zerocash" protocol.
 Based on Bitcoin's code, it intends to offer a far higher standard
 of privacy and anonymity through a sophisticiated zero-knowledge
 proving scheme which preserves confidentiality of transaction metadata.
 This package provides the daemon, zcashd, and the CLI tool,
 zcash-cli, to interact with the daemon.
 .
 This package provides zcashd, a combined daemon and CLI tool to
 interact with the daemon.
